dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill run out (Shadab Khan/Sarfaraz Ahmed) 45 (62b 4x4 1x6 86m) SR: 72.58

dismissalComment.html: a horrific mix-up. Oh, dear! They did all the hardwork by consolidating and now have fallen to bad communication. A full legbreak that was driven out to deep point. Williamson wants the second but Guptill isn't sure. Williamson continues on his way and Guptill responds. But it's so late that they're almost at the same end. The throw comes on to Sarfraz's end who then underarms it to the bowler who gathers it and takes out the stumps even as Guptill puts in a full-length dive

dismissalComment.html: now all of a sudden Pakistan decide to come alive and that has resulted in a run out. A short of a length delivery that is punched to sweeper cover. commentPostTextItems.html: 5.10pm You want abject? You want abysmal? You got 27.2 overs of it. Another limp batting performance from Pakistan, their approach was flawed, planning wrong and execution appalling. It all culminated in a terrible batting display from Pakistan as they were bowled out for 74, losing by 183 runs to also surrender the series in meek fashion.

New Zealand are very rarely indisciplined. Like always, they started well again today, and some lateral movement helped. But Pakistan's block-block-hit approach just won't work, and it showed today. There will be two dead rubbers to come, as New Zealand take the series as quickly as they can.
Trent Boult is the Man of the Match: "Pretty windy today, the wind was behind me today. Collective effort. Wanted to get the series done, knew we had to fight hard with only 250 on the board."
Sarfraz Ahmed: "A tough loss, batting was again flop. We will sit together and sort it out. The problem is the new ball. We'll not give so many wickets in the first 10 overs.

Kane Williamson: "Fantastic performance all around, a tough surface to get in on. Tim and Trent to start off, just built up that pressure. It was really tough to score. Just a slowish surface. It was going to be hard to score. We knew it will be tough, but we wanted to execute our skills. The focus is the next game.
